Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveWhatIfTimingAssertions(25.10)            saveWhatIfTimingAssertions(25.10)

Name
       saveWhatIfTimingAssertions  -  Writes timing arcs to the specified file
       or Tcl list

Syntax
        saveWhatIfTimingAssertions

       [<blackBoxCellName>]

       -outfile <fileName> | -tclList

       Writes timing arcs to the specified file or Tcl list. The Innovus soft-
       ware saves the final state of the timing arc. The history  of  all  the
       modifications is not saved. You can source the generated file, regroup-
       ing the whole timing arc specifications of the blackbox or blackblob in
       a new Innovus session.

       You can use this command after the module definition of the blackbox or
       the blackblob is available with the I/O's in the Verilog netlist.

Parameters
       <blackBoxCellName>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the blackbox or blackblob cell. If the
              name is not specified, all timing arc specifications are saved.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the output file in which to save  the  in-
              formation.

       -tclList
              Generates  the timing arcs as a Tcl list. The Tcl list is useful
              for integrating what-if timing with custom Tcl functions.

Related Information
              * What-If Timing Analysis chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                     * Performing What-If Timing Analysis

                     * Using the What-If Timing Commands

